# Runtime Configuration

## Main Scripts
- [scripts/start.sh](mdc:scripts/start.sh): Main entry point for the container
  - Monitors WiFi connectivity every minute
  - Starts/stops the captive portal based on connection status
  - Sources functions from start-network.sh

- [scripts/start-network.sh](mdc:scripts/start-network.sh): Network utilities
  - Sets up network services for captive portal operation
  - Provides functions to verify captive portal functionality
  - Checks internet connectivity through multiple methods

## Operational Flow
1. On container start, [start.sh](mdc:scripts/start.sh) checks for WiFi connection
2. If connected, it monitors for disconnections every minute
3. If disconnected, it starts wifi-connect in captive portal mode
4. When a connection is established, the portal is stopped
5. This cycle continues, providing automatic recovery from disconnections

## Captive Portal Verification
- The portal operates on IP 192.168.42.1:80
- Verification uses curl to check server responsiveness
- Internet connectivity is verified via:
  - NetworkManager connectivity state
  - ICMP ping to 8.8.8.8
  - DNS resolution test

## Environmental Requirements
- Requires dbus access for NetworkManager communications
- Needs root/privileged access for network interface manipulation
- Container must have access to host networking
